1
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,570
[Xiacheng Pier]

2
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:16,340
We're finally here.

3
00:00:16,340 --> 00:00:17,540
Yeah, I'm exhausted.

4
00:00:33,190 --> 00:00:42,930
[Xiacheng Pier]

5
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,110
Do you want to go back to Xiacheng?

6
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,120
What kind of question is that?
Of course I do.

7
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:51,050
I don't want to go back to Xiacheng.

8
00:00:51,490 --> 00:00:53,950
I don't really have anything
tying me there.

9
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:56,890
You can go back for me.

10
00:00:58,030 --> 00:01:02,050
♪ The setting sun sinks low into the sea ♪

11
00:00:58,950 --> 00:00:59,740
Shrimpie.

12
00:01:01,740 --> 00:01:03,740
Looks like you were wrong after all.

13
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,160
We still came back together.

14
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:07,130
♪ And the ship goes down into the flames ♪

15
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:10,090
Zhang Haixia, don't worry.

16
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:11,090
♪ You're standing by my side ♪

17
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:11,220
Stick with me,

18
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,170
and we'll make a name for ourselves
in Balongzhou.

19
00:01:14,170 --> 00:01:17,770
♪ Time is like a plague,
devouring yesterday ♪

20
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,450
When the time comes,
we'll return to Xiacheng in glory

21
00:01:16,450 --> 00:01:17,850
and see Mentor together.

22
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:19,010
Let's go, Shrimpie.

23
00:01:20,110 --> 00:01:22,730
♪ Yet I've searched through
every archive ♪

24
00:01:20,810 --> 00:01:21,730
Balongzhou,

25
00:01:23,110 --> 00:01:23,970
here we come!

26
00:01:24,350 --> 00:01:26,020
♪ Filled with endless lies ♪

27
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:32,570
♪ The opening pages of this story
are woven from deceit ♪

28
00:01:33,090 --> 00:01:35,979
♪ A trial written into fate ♪

29
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:42,810
♪ Through the mist I search your face—
are you still the same? ♪

30
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:48,200
♪ The wind carries away the goodbye
we never said ♪

31
00:01:46,450 --> 00:01:49,720
[Inquiry Office]

32
00:01:49,090 --> 00:01:51,890
♪ The butterfly upon your shoulder ♪

33
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:51,180
Plague!

34
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:58,160
♪ Stayed with you to witness
this bustling world ♪

35
00:01:57,770 --> 00:01:59,229
You're heading to Jinfan?

36
00:01:59,250 --> 00:01:59,740
Yes.

37
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:01,640
What about you?

38
00:02:02,180 --> 00:02:03,180
What's your plan?

39
00:02:05,260 --> 00:02:07,460
I'll take him back to the Archives first

40
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:08,780
and look for Mentor.

41
00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:10,460
I wonder if Mentor still remembers

42
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:11,390
what I look like.

43
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:13,770
That's good.

44
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:17,070
I won't be in need of this money anyway
now that I'm back.

45
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:19,670
Switch to a bigger ship
for your trip to Jinfan.

46
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,730
You know I won't take it.

47
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:22,950
I have my own money.

48
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:24,600
This is a principle.

49
00:02:27,140 --> 00:02:28,780
What needed repaying has been repaid,

50
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:31,310
and what needed resenting
has been resented.

51
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:33,160
Farewell.

52
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,310
Give this money to Zhang Hailou.

53
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:52,870
He's the Plague of Nanyang.

54
00:02:54,329 --> 00:02:54,940
It's him.

55
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,500
Plague!

56
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:57,750
Plague...

57
00:02:58,710 --> 00:02:59,430
Plague!

58
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,190
Be careful.

59
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:04,150
Plague!

60
00:03:04,420 --> 00:03:05,160
Plague!

61
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:38,630
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

62
00:04:38,890 --> 00:04:41,510
[Episode 11]

63
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:48,510
Plague!

64
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:52,500
Hello.

65
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,159
Did you see someone coming out from here?

66
00:04:54,159 --> 00:04:54,770
Wearing a uniform,

67
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:55,890
carrying someone on his back?

68
00:04:55,890 --> 00:04:57,470
No. Go check over there.

69
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,320
Thank you.

70
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:01,110
Hello, sir. Did you

71
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:02,330
see someone

72
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:03,330
coming out from here,

73
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:04,360
wearing a uniform,

74
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,220
and carrying someone on his back?

75
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,100
No, I didn't.

76
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:07,980
No, no, I didn't.

77
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:08,690
Thank you.

78
00:05:12,690 --> 00:05:13,250
Sir.

79
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,600
Hello, sir.

80
00:05:15,130 --> 00:05:16,120
Did you see

81
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,680
a man in a uniform coming out from here,

82
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,340
carrying someone on his back?

83
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,720
I saw you on the ship.

84
00:05:21,810 --> 00:05:23,760
You were with that tall guy.

85
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:25,050
You guys got separated, right?

86
00:05:25,050 --> 00:05:25,980
Yes, yes, that's right.

87
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:26,770
He's my friend.

88
00:05:26,770 --> 00:05:28,600
Did you see which way he went?

89
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,220
No, I didn't.

90
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,180
But

91
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:35,290
I'd like to borrow something from you.

92
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:36,890
Borrow something?

93
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:38,540
Money?

94
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,740
I have no money.

95
00:05:40,930 --> 00:05:42,040
I'm in a hurry to find my friend.

96
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:44,040
His friend left some money with me,

97
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,500
so I need to bring it to him.

98
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,540
It's not money.

99
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:47,659
S-Sir.

100
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,909
Pardon me.

101
00:05:48,940 --> 00:05:50,310
I'm still in a hurry to find my friend,

102
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:51,880
and I have a ship to catch soon.

103
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,060
If you don't know,

104
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,000
I won't bother you further.

105
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,600
Thank you.

106
00:05:54,930 --> 00:05:56,310
Since that's the case,

107
00:05:56,590 --> 00:05:58,990
I can help you give the money
to your friend.

108
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,220
You?

109
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,180
I don't even know you.

110
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,510
What do you want?

111
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:06,220
Since you're so worried,

112
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,620
I can exchange my money

113
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,690
with yours.

114
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,240
However,

115
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:13,980
I'd still like to borrow something
from you.

116
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:15,910
What exactly do you want to borrow?

117
00:06:19,370 --> 00:06:20,040
Your face.

118
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,280
What's your problem?

119
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:36,330
[Xiacheng Pier]

120
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:49,480
Hurry up.

121
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:50,430
Move.

122
00:06:52,110 --> 00:06:52,880
Move, move.

123
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:59,330
Master, Young Lady's back.

124
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:14,770
Sweetie.

125
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:23,980
[Xiacheng Pier]

126
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,870
Dad, I'm back.

127
00:07:18,330 --> 00:07:21,620
Did you have a smooth trip, Sweetie?

128
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:24,630
Thanks to Mr. Warner's escort,

129
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,240
I was able to arrive safely in Xiacheng.

130
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:29,870
Mr. Dong, I am Landon Warner.

131
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,190
I'm Miss Dong's business partner.

132
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:36,610
[Xiacheng Pier]

133
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,630
It's a pleasure to meet you.

134
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:34,430
I hope

135
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:36,830
we'll have a pleasant cooperation
in our future business.

136
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,720
I'm old now,

137
00:07:38,659 --> 00:07:41,260
and I washed my hands of foreign trade
long ago.

138
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,210
Now I just run a few small trades

139
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:46,420
and wait for my daughter
to take over the family business.

140
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:49,310
I'm afraid,

141
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,600
Mr. Warner, your business

142
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:53,840
might not be easy for me to take on.

143
00:07:56,220 --> 00:07:58,000
Your daughter used my musketeers

144
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,760
to round up so many pirates in Nan'an.

145
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:02,220
As you Chinese say,

146
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:04,010
"boldness stems from superb skill."

147
00:08:04,010 --> 00:08:07,540
She's really a worthy daughter
of Shichang, the shipping king.

148
00:08:08,010 --> 00:08:09,360
In those containers,

149
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,000
there are many

150
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,740
unidentified corpses.

151
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:13,500
If the police ask about this,

152
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:14,360
should I say

153
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:16,430
they're related to the Dong family

154
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:17,450
or not?

155
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:22,500
It's all my fault.

156
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,570
I've spent my whole life doing business

157
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:26,750
and made many enemies along the way,

158
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:29,660
and now I even got my daughter
dragged into it.

159
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:31,010
However,

160
00:08:31,790 --> 00:08:33,770
this is my hometown.

161
00:08:35,289 --> 00:08:36,049
If anyone

162
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:40,789
dares to scheme against or threaten me
here,

163
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:41,980
I'll make sure

164
00:08:42,549 --> 00:08:44,860
they don't leave Xiacheng alive.

165
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:53,200
You must be exhausted from the journey.

166
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,140
Mr. Warner, please get in the car.

167
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:56,560
Let's head back and rest.

168
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:57,740
Please.

169
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:07,600
Please take the car behind.

170
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:10,860
Our Master and Young Lady
still have some catching up to do.

171
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:14,580
[Xiacheng Pier]

172
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:15,610
Get ready to leave, boys!

173
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:20,000
Aren't we supposed to take the initiation?

174
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,290
So? We're still doing business with them?

175
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:23,460
Yes, of course.

176
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,390
I don't believe

177
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:26,320
Victory will always be on her side.

178
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,150
Finally back.

179
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:51,380
Why did you suddenly
return to Xiacheng this time

180
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:53,940
with so many foreigners?

181
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:55,290
Did something happen?

182
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:58,850
Have you made any progress

183
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:01,180
on what I asked you to investigate?

184
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:04,770
All the information you requested is here.

185
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:10,040
[Map of Xiacheng City]

186
00:10:04,890 --> 00:10:06,220
I've had someone decrypt

187
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:07,740
the telegram you sent me

188
00:10:08,490 --> 00:10:10,230
from the Nan'an.

189
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,210
It was encrypted

190
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,980
with a military encryption method.

191
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:16,190
This telegram

192
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:18,720
was sent to a warlord force,

193
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,500
but

194
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:22,100
that unit is rather unusual.

195
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,050
You truly are a man of the military.

196
00:10:24,050 --> 00:10:25,180
Unusual in what way?

197
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:26,510
They keep

198
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,420
an extremely low profile.

199
00:10:28,820 --> 00:10:31,950
The information that can be discovered
is very limited.

200
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:35,650
They were last seen around Beilian,

201
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:38,820
led by a man named Mo Yungao.

202
00:10:39,890 --> 00:10:41,620
We're only sure of his name,

203
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:45,000
but there isn't even
a single clear photo of him.

204
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:50,110
The final part of
this decrypted telegram says,

205
00:10:50,340 --> 00:10:52,930
"Members of the Southern Archives
have been eliminated.

206
00:10:50,970 --> 00:10:53,020
[Telegram Draft]

207
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:55,030
All bodies have been recovered.

208
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:57,320
Will meet in Xiacheng as agreed.

209
00:10:57,890 --> 00:10:59,750
This telegram serves as notice."

210
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,880
Mo Yungao?

211
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,880
So you're the one
messing with my Archives.

212
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:21,180
It seems a bloodbath
is coming to Xiacheng.

213
00:11:38,930 --> 00:11:40,590
This street is still the same.

214
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:46,200
Zhang Hailou.

215
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:47,470
If you keep crying,

216
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,860
I won't carry you anymore.

217
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:52,040
Zhang Haixia, walk faster, okay?

218
00:11:52,060 --> 00:11:52,670
Okay.

219
00:11:53,460 --> 00:11:54,290
Zhang Hailou,

220
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,500
watch your mouth!

221
00:11:55,860 --> 00:11:57,320
As if I owed you something.

222
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:58,470
Seriously.

223
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,450
I don't believe I can't handle you!

224
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,200
I was wrong!

225
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:14,210
[A Hundred Flowers in Bloom]

226
00:12:10,790 --> 00:12:11,430
Shrimpie.

227
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:13,460
We've arrived.

228
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:22,890
Sir,

229
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,140
what do you need?

230
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,100
Who are you?

231
00:12:28,340 --> 00:12:29,600
Why are you in my house?

232
00:12:30,010 --> 00:12:32,760
I sell dried seafood.

233
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:35,290
Did you come to the wrong place?

234
00:12:43,660 --> 00:12:45,520
What about the previous tenants?

235
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,560
I've been

236
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:48,260
running this shop for years.

237
00:12:48,610 --> 00:12:49,930
No one has lived here.

238
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:52,970
I used to live here.

239
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,900
But it was a long time ago.

240
00:12:57,180 --> 00:12:59,470
Maybe your family moved away.

241
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:05,640
[Yuanbao Clinic]

242
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:05,000
Moving away without even
leaving a message—

243
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,460
that's typical of Mentor.

244
00:13:07,070 --> 00:13:07,740
Shrimpie,

245
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,370
let's go to the Archives.

246
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,290
[Yuanbao Clinic]

247
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:21,650
[Danan Telegraph Office]

248
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,940
I throw more accurately than you.

249
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:16,070
You throw terribly!

250
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:30,580
Zhang Hailou, Zhang Haixia!

251
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,460
Mentor's here.

252
00:13:31,530 --> 00:13:32,360
Come here.

253
00:13:34,850 --> 00:13:35,870
Mentor.

254
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:38,110
Why does the front of the Archives

255
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,790
say "Telegraph Office"?

256
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:45,620
Because the Archives
is a secret organization

257
00:13:45,620 --> 00:13:47,270
directly under
the Maritime Supervisory Office.

258
00:13:47,270 --> 00:13:48,870
We must not let ordinary people
know about it,

259
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:50,270
so it has to be disguised.

260
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:51,220
Mentor!

261
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:52,790
Did you hear that?

262
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:53,840
This is a secret.

263
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:56,490
To the public, we are
Danan Telegraph Office.

264
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,240
But Mentor,

265
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:01,060
will this really keep us
from being discovered?

266
00:14:02,380 --> 00:14:05,230
Within an organization
vast and complex enough,

267
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:07,720
there are always redundant departments.

268
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,150
As long as we hide in such places,

269
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:10,480
we stay under the radar.

270
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,320
Just like hermit crabs.

271
00:14:15,950 --> 00:14:16,670
Mentor,

272
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:19,060
when can I go play in the Archives?

273
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,250
Focus on learning the ropes first.

274
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:23,150
Once you become a full employee,
you'll be allowed into the Archives.

275
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,050
Let's go home.

276
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:31,990
[Danan Telegraph Office]

277
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:30,700
Zhang Hailou.

278
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:35,770
Stop there!

279
00:14:35,820 --> 00:14:36,720
Come catch me!

280
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,910
This is really nice.

281
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:45,510
[Haili Bank]

282
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:39,860
Let me see.

283
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:40,630
If you don't like it,
there's also this one.

284
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:41,290
Never mind.

285
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:42,000
Just take a look.

286
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,470
These are all good stuff.

287
00:14:51,380 --> 00:14:53,530
[Haili Bank]

288
00:14:54,290 --> 00:14:55,390
Are these all registered?

289
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:56,390
Yes, don't worry.

290
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:57,320
You can just come directly.

291
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:57,650
Okay.

292
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:59,200
I'll come to you again next time.

293
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,200
He will receive you.

294
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,200
You can also talk to me in the future.

295
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:04,650
Hello, ma'am.

296
00:15:04,790 --> 00:15:06,270
You need to register here.

297
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:07,240
Here, right?

298
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:07,740
Yes.

299
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:08,200
Okay.

300
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:10,360
Sir.

301
00:15:11,430 --> 00:15:13,060
Sir, how can I help you?

302
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,410
Wasn't this place
the Danan Telegraph Office before?

303
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:17,690
How did it become a bank?

304
00:15:17,690 --> 00:15:19,040
Sir, this place has always been a bank.

305
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,790
I've never heard of a telegraph office.

306
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:22,220
Did you get the wrong place?

307
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:22,750
That's impossible.

308
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,390
I worked here for many years.

309
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:27,360
I couldn't have remembered it wrong.

310
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,220
How many years have you been open?

311
00:15:29,290 --> 00:15:30,620
It's been quite a few years.

312
00:15:30,620 --> 00:15:32,430
But as for what it was before we opened,

313
00:15:32,430 --> 00:15:33,290
I'm not so sure.

314
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:34,400
I'm sorry, sir.

315
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:36,960
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

316
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:49,890
[Maritime Supervisory Office]

317
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:52,650
This is
the Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office.

318
00:15:52,650 --> 00:15:54,450
Okay, I'll check for you in a bit.

319
00:16:01,410 --> 00:16:01,960
Hello.

320
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:05,640
Excuse me, do you know

321
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:08,400
where the Southern Archives moved to?

322
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:10,230
The Southern Archives?

323
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:12,640
Have you heard of it?

324
00:16:12,770 --> 00:16:13,770
Never heard of it.

325
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:14,760
What Archives?

326
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,880
This is
the Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office.

327
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:22,250
Here's the thing.

328
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:24,370
The Southern Archives is

329
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:27,100
an agency under
the Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office.

330
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,410
Since it's a...

331
00:16:31,020 --> 00:16:33,250
Since it's
a secret investigation organization,

332
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:34,790
it has always used

333
00:16:34,810 --> 00:16:37,340
the name "Danan Telegraph Office"
as a cover.

334
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:39,010
Actually, broadly speaking,

335
00:16:39,550 --> 00:16:40,600
we can be considered colleagues.

336
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,600
Now that I have returned to the country,

337
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,840
I found that
the Southern Archives has moved,

338
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,550
but I don't know where it moved to.

339
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:46,210
Could you please check for me?

340
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,030
Please wait a moment.

341
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:49,480
Okay.

342
00:17:17,910 --> 00:17:18,569
Sir,

343
00:17:18,619 --> 00:17:19,430
I've asked around.

344
00:17:19,430 --> 00:17:21,960
There is no such "Archives"
as you mentioned.

345
00:17:22,109 --> 00:17:23,310
How is that possible?

346
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:25,290
The name is "the Southern Archives."

347
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:26,460
You must have gotten it wrong.

348
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:27,680
I just asked some senior commissioners

349
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,810
who have worked here for over 20 years,

350
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:30,850
and they said that in all these years

351
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:33,330
since Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office
was established,

352
00:17:33,330 --> 00:17:35,690
there has never been an agency called

353
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,180
"the Southern Archives."

354
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:38,420
Are you mistaken?

355
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:44,210
It must be you who are mistaken.

356
00:17:44,210 --> 00:17:48,810
[Inquiry Desk]

357
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:47,460
Please keep an eye on my brother for me.

358
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:48,520
I'll go ask myself.

359
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:49,500
Sir!

360
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:52,590
What do you mean

361
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:54,420
the Southern Archives never existed?

362
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:56,290
Look, if it doesn't exist,
it doesn't exist.

363
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:58,620
We've never heard of any Archives either.

364
00:17:58,940 --> 00:17:59,570
Young man,

365
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:00,380
look,

366
00:18:00,910 --> 00:18:02,190
this is our file.

367
00:18:02,050 --> 00:18:04,520
[Files of
the Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office]

368
00:18:05,270 --> 00:18:06,670
Absolutely impossible.

369
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,350
I was trained and employed
at the Southern Archives

370
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:10,150
for over 10 years.

371
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:12,110
[Registry of Affiliated Agencies
Reporting to the Maritime Supervisory Office]

372
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,230
I've always been an agent here,

373
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:14,410
and I even worked in the office of
the Archives.

374
00:18:14,410 --> 00:18:15,640
I've handled countless mysterious cases.

375
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,380
Every file should be on record.

376
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:16,300
[Registry of Affiliated Agencies
Reporting to the Maritime Supervisory Office]

377
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:18,810
Look.

378
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:20,790
This is my badge.

379
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:23,830
[Zhang Hailou]

380
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:25,170
We've never issued any badge like this.

381
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:25,990
Besides,

382
00:18:26,170 --> 00:18:27,710
we manage ship crews here.

383
00:18:28,070 --> 00:18:30,400
Investigations are none of our business.

384
00:18:36,330 --> 00:18:36,850
Let go!

385
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:39,120
Say it!

386
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,800
Where is the Southern Archives?

387
00:18:41,980 --> 00:18:42,610
Speak!

388
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:45,740
I really don't know anything about

389
00:18:46,190 --> 00:18:48,210
the Southern Archives.

390
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,070
You are lying!

391
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:53,890
I'm not lying...

392
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:56,060
I'm telling the truth...

393
00:18:58,050 --> 00:19:00,110
I'm telling the truth...

394
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:06,930
If you're not lying,

395
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:13,290
then the Southern Archives doesn't exist.

396
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:14,490
How is that possible?

397
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:25,030
If the Southern Archives doesn't exist,

398
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:30,240
then what do the past decades
of my life amount to?

399
00:19:30,590 --> 00:19:32,470
Commissioner , what happened?

400
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:35,910
Why would Mentor lie to me?

401
00:19:45,860 --> 00:19:51,460
[Maritime Supervisory Office]

402
00:19:49,150 --> 00:19:50,260
Leave immediately. Move.

403
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:52,460
There's no one here you are looking for.

404
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,050
Shrimpie. Careful.

405
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:03,230
[Archives Room]

406
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:04,550
Speak!

407
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:05,160
Let go!

408
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:08,830
You're lying!

409
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:13,960
[Maritime Supervisory Office]

410
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:14,260
Come check this out,
fresh roasted sweet potatoes!

411
00:20:14,290 --> 00:20:16,740
Soft and sweet roasted sweet potatoes!

412
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:20,380
Freshly roasted sweet potatoes!

413
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:24,180
Soft and sweet roasted sweet potatoes!

414
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,720
Please keep an eye on my brother for me
for a bit.

415
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,430
Okay, okay.

416
00:20:33,790 --> 00:20:37,080
[Archives Room]

417
00:21:02,380 --> 00:21:02,680
[Files]

418
00:22:06,570 --> 00:22:08,330
Mom, what are we having today?

419
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,140
We're having stir-fried shrimp today.

420
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:11,140
Let's hurry home!

421
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:13,680
Okay. Let's go.

422
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,700
Let's hurry home!

423
00:22:16,330 --> 00:22:17,500
Let's go!

424
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:31,050
[Dehexing]

425
00:23:05,110 --> 00:23:07,040
I finally brought you home, but now

426
00:23:08,910 --> 00:23:10,710
the home's gone, the job's gone,

427
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:13,020
and the Archives doesn't even exist.

428
00:23:14,270 --> 00:23:15,270
Do you believe it?

429
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:24,940
Well, I sure don't.

430
00:23:26,660 --> 00:23:28,250
According to the newspapers,

431
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:29,560
the Chen warlords

432
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:33,010
have gained complete control of Xiacheng.

433
00:23:33,010 --> 00:23:34,660
We've sent 36

434
00:23:34,660 --> 00:23:35,890
regular monthly report telegrams,

435
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:37,350
but there's been no reply.

436
00:23:37,350 --> 00:23:38,480
The last one was sent

437
00:23:39,090 --> 00:23:41,090
after we came back from Panhua Reef.

438
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:43,000
Maybe something happened to the Archives,

439
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:43,940
or someone

440
00:23:43,940 --> 00:23:45,220
erased its existence.

441
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:48,160
Even if it was erased,

442
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:50,090
how could it be done so thoroughly?

443
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:54,030
Could this be the work of
whoever's spreading that toxic weed?

444
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,410
[Chocolate]

445
00:24:15,330 --> 00:24:16,470
Times are hard.

446
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:17,640
We won't meet again.

447
00:24:18,190 --> 00:24:19,660
If your obsession persists

448
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:21,260
and you are still perplexed,

449
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,210
you may come here for a chat.

450
00:24:23,810 --> 00:24:24,410
Remember,

451
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:25,920
it's best we don't meet.

452
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,720
Nothing needs to be said anyway.

453
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:31,380
This woman is so resourceful.

454
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:34,240
Maybe I should ask her for help.

455
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:43,720
The Southern Archives?

456
00:24:52,870 --> 00:24:54,280
Sir, this way please.

457
00:24:56,990 --> 00:24:58,420
My Lady, he's here.

458
00:25:14,410 --> 00:25:15,720
I thought you'd wander out there

459
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:16,590
for a few weeks

460
00:25:16,590 --> 00:25:17,720
before coming to me.

461
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:20,010
I didn't expect you to come so soon.

462
00:25:21,250 --> 00:25:22,580
Are your wounds healed?

463
00:25:23,810 --> 00:25:25,670
All the doctors on your ship died.

464
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:27,740
I treated my wounds myself.

465
00:25:27,740 --> 00:25:29,940
I don't think they could heal very well.

466
00:25:39,750 --> 00:25:41,350
Miss Dong, I have a question.

467
00:25:43,790 --> 00:25:45,120
When we were on the ship,

468
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,810
you refused to talk to me.

469
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,450
But after getting off the ship,

470
00:25:51,030 --> 00:25:52,690
you wrote me that invitation.

471
00:25:54,510 --> 00:25:55,550
Hermit crabs.

472
00:25:57,810 --> 00:25:59,140
The Southern Archives.

473
00:26:01,050 --> 00:26:02,310
Do you know something?

474
00:26:04,460 --> 00:26:06,460
I've never heard of any "Archives."

475
00:26:07,050 --> 00:26:08,590
Did you have a dream or something?

476
00:26:08,590 --> 00:26:10,030
The former Danan Telegraph Office

477
00:26:10,030 --> 00:26:11,290
was the Southern Archives.

478
00:26:11,290 --> 00:26:13,310
My mentor, Zhang Haiqi,

479
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,500
was the Director of it.

480
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:16,590
Where is she now?

481
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:19,100
And where did the Southern Archives
move to?

482
00:26:19,470 --> 00:26:21,730
I have no idea what you're talking about.

483
00:26:26,740 --> 00:26:27,420
Miss Dong.

484
00:26:28,940 --> 00:26:30,600
You kept me alive on that ship.

485
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,610
If you need me to get anything done,

486
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:35,750
you can just tell me.

487
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:38,940
But right now, I just need to know

488
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:44,810
that the existence of
the Southern Archives meant something,

489
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:46,850
so my friend didn't die for nothing.

490
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:50,010
Even if it's gone now,

491
00:26:50,660 --> 00:26:52,920
I could accept it
as a cruel twist of fate.

492
00:26:53,590 --> 00:26:56,320
My only fear is that
after everything we've done,

493
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:58,740
it turns out to be nothing but a daydream,

494
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:02,820
and no one will even remember.

495
00:27:13,230 --> 00:27:14,760
Let me tell you a story then.

496
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:17,700
Once upon a time, there were two agents.

497
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,500
One was smart,

498
00:27:22,180 --> 00:27:22,910
and the other

499
00:27:23,610 --> 00:27:24,850
was a troublemaker.

500
00:27:26,270 --> 00:27:27,930
The two of them were partners,

501
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:30,370
investigating cases everywhere.

502
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,300
They solved many cases together.

503
00:27:33,250 --> 00:27:34,610
But the troublemaker

504
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:36,800
was always causing trouble,

505
00:27:37,050 --> 00:27:38,280
and the smart one

506
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:41,030
had to constantly clean up his messes.

507
00:27:41,510 --> 00:27:43,110
Many years passed like this.

508
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:45,830
During a case on a reef,

509
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:47,940
the two agents

510
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,600
went deep into the enemy's stronghold.

511
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,600
There were many enemies,

512
00:27:53,270 --> 00:27:55,300
and there were only 2 of them.

513
00:27:58,130 --> 00:28:01,810
They should have retreated right after
they finished searching for evidence,

514
00:28:01,810 --> 00:28:03,160
but the troublemaker

515
00:28:03,180 --> 00:28:04,530
acted on his own.

516
00:28:04,990 --> 00:28:06,740
To get more information,

517
00:28:07,030 --> 00:28:09,040
he did something very risky.

518
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:12,750
He actually revealed his identity
to the enemy,

519
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:15,310
leaking the Archives' information
to the enemy.

520
00:28:15,310 --> 00:28:17,570
Have you heard of a man
named Salty Zhang?

521
00:28:17,750 --> 00:28:18,810
This guy belongs to

522
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:22,920
the Southern Archives under
the Nanyang Maritime Supervisory Office.

523
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:24,110
Yet it was precisely

524
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:25,910
this small, unnecessary action

525
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,940
that ultimately led to a great disaster.

526
00:28:29,330 --> 00:28:31,190
Because he exposed his identity,

527
00:28:31,330 --> 00:28:32,090
the enemy quickly found

528
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:34,330
the headquarters of the Archives.

529
00:28:34,490 --> 00:28:35,750
The enemy moved so fast

530
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,590
that the headquarters
was caught off guard.

531
00:28:37,590 --> 00:28:38,770
Overnight,

532
00:28:39,090 --> 00:28:41,790
all the agents at the headquarters
were slaughtered,

533
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:43,660
and the agents scattered everywhere

534
00:28:43,660 --> 00:28:46,390
were also continuously hunted down
by the enemy—

535
00:28:46,990 --> 00:28:48,790
until they found these 2 agents.

536
00:28:50,330 --> 00:28:52,130
The troublemaker survived,

537
00:28:53,090 --> 00:28:54,070
but the smart one

538
00:28:55,470 --> 00:28:56,470
failed to escape.

539
00:29:00,870 --> 00:29:01,980
Are you finished?

540
00:29:02,560 --> 00:29:03,570
Why so impatient?

541
00:29:03,870 --> 00:29:06,400
I haven't got to the best part
of the story yet.

542
00:29:07,030 --> 00:29:08,180
The story goes

543
00:29:09,170 --> 00:29:10,860
that the smart agent,

544
00:29:11,230 --> 00:29:13,950
in the closing report of the reef case,

545
00:29:14,530 --> 00:29:16,130
wrote a paragraph like this.

546
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,730
It's on your right side.

547
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:23,040
Would you like to have a read?

548
00:29:43,510 --> 00:29:47,070
[Major Oversight]
[Conclusions and Warnings]

549
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:45,240
The Panhua Reef Case

550
00:29:45,610 --> 00:29:46,700
is still pending,

551
00:29:47,330 --> 00:29:48,390
full of mysteries.

552
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:50,310
During the operation,

553
00:29:50,530 --> 00:29:53,240
the agents' identities
and the Archives' information were leaked,

554
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:54,510
which could cause future trouble.

555
00:29:54,510 --> 00:29:55,840
I hope Director is aware

556
00:29:55,850 --> 00:29:56,980
so that countermeasures can be prepared.

557
00:29:56,130 --> 00:29:58,730
[Case Closure Report]

558
00:29:58,810 --> 00:30:00,310
[Major Oversight]
[Conclusions and Warnings]

559
00:29:59,140 --> 00:30:01,000
As for the oversight in this case,

560
00:30:01,570 --> 00:30:03,900
I'm willing to bear full responsibility.

561
00:30:23,330 --> 00:30:23,900
Alright.

562
00:30:25,370 --> 00:30:26,830
That's the end of my story.

563
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:28,780
You may leave now.

564
00:30:38,950 --> 00:30:40,000
Who exactly are you?
